billingServer
Class BillingServerSecure

java.lang.Object
  billingServer.BillingServerSecure
All Implemented Interfaces:
BillingServerSecureInterface, java.io.Serializable, java.rmi.Remote
public class BillingServerSecure
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, BillingServerSecureInterface

This class provides methodes to delete, create and get the current Pricesteps. To that, there can be created a bill, when the auction is over. This bill can be lookuped by the specific username.

createPriceStep

public boolean createPriceStep(double startPrice,
                               double endPrice,
                               double fixedPrice,
                               double variablePricePercent)
                        throws java.rmi.RemoteException,
                               InvalidParameterException,
                               InvalidInputException,
                               OverlappedPricestepException
This method creates a new pricestep, if the new pricestep doesnt overlap with existing ones. If the new pricestep overlaps, you have to delete the old one first. All parameters have to be > 0

Specified by:
createPriceStep in interface BillingServerSecureInterface
Parameters:
startPrice - startprice of the new pricestep
endPrice - endprice of the new pricestep
fixedPrice - fixedprice of the new pricestep
variablePricePercent - variablePricePercent of the new pricestep
Returns:
boolean true, if the new pricestep has been successfully set. otherwise throw RemoteException
Throws:
java.rmi.RemoteException - thrown when parameter < 0 or overlaping with existing pricestep
InvalidParameterException
InvalidInputException
OverlappedPricestepException
